{"word":"ἔα","slug":"ἔα","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ἔα</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ cp.\">cp.</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ Lat.\">Lat.</a> sine] exclamatory particle expressing surprise or displeasure, with arresting emphasis <b><i>Ho! Aha!</i> <a href='B:480 1:24'>Mk 1:24</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ v.l.\">v.l.</a>; <a href='B:490 4:34'>Lk 4:34</a>.</b> In these passages there may be some connection with <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἔα\">ἔα</a></el>, <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ impv.\">impv.</a> of <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἐάω\">ἐάω</a></el>, and the form may be rendered <i>Stop!</i> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:εʹ\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ἐάν\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}